#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:5
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:7
msgid ""
"A UV texture is a picture (image, sequence or movie) that is used to color "
"the surface of a mesh. The UV texture is mapped to the mesh through one or "
"more UV maps. There are three ways to establish the image used by the UV "
"texture:"
msgstr ""
"Une texture UV est une illustration (image, séquence ou film) qui est "
"utilisée pour colorer la surface d'un maillage. La texture UV est reportée "
"sur le maillage à travers un ou plusieurs UV maps. Il y a trois manières "
"d'établir l'image utilisée par la texture UV."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:12
msgid ""
"Paint a flat image in the UV/Image Editor onto the currently selected UV "
"texture, using its UV map to transfer the colors to the faces of the mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:14
msgid ""
"Paint the mesh in the 3D View, and let Blender use the currently selected UV "
"map to update the UV texture (see :ref:`Projection Painting <painting-"
"texture-index>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:16
msgid ""
"Use any image editing program to create an image. In the UV/Image Editor, "
"select the UV texture and load the image. Blender will then use that "
"texture's UV map to transfer the colors to the faces of the mesh."
msgstr ""
"utilisez n'importe quel programme d'édition d'image pour créer une image. "
"Dans l'Éditeur UV/Image, sélectionnez la texture UV et chargez l'image. "
"Blender va alors utiliser l'UV map de cette texture pour trnsférer les "
"couleurs sur les faces du maillage."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:20
msgid ""
"Blender features a built-in paint mode called *Texture Paint* which is "
"designed specifically to help you edit your UV textures and images quickly "
"and easily in either the UV/Image or the 3D View Editor. Since a UV texture "
"is just a special-purpose image, you can also use any external paint "
"program. For example, GIMP is a full-featured image manipulation program "
"that is also open-source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:30
msgid "Texture painting in Blender."
msgstr "Peinture de texture dans Blender."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:32
msgid ""
"Since a mesh can have layers of UV textures, there may be many images that "
"color the mesh. However, each UV texture only has one image."
msgstr ""
"Étant donné qu'un maillage puisse avoir des calques de textures UV, il se "
"peut qu'il y ait beaucoup d'images qui colorent le maillage. Cependant, "
"chaque texture UV a une seule image. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:35
msgid ""
"*Texture Paint* works in both a 3D View and the UV/Image Editor. In the 3D "
"View in Texture Paint Mode, you paint directly on the mesh by :ref:"
"`projecting onto the UVs <painting-texture-index>`."
msgstr ""
"*Texture Paint* fonction à la fois en Vue 3D et dans l'Éditeur UV/Image. En "
"Vue 3D en *Mode Texture Paint*, vous peignez directement sur le maillage en :"
"ref:`projetant sur les UV <painting-texture-index>`."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/texture_paint/introduction.rst:41
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr "Mise en route"

